        <section id="uses-comp">
            <h>complement</h>
            <!--<p>Like other nouns, <g>achadh</g> can be used as the complement of a <a
                href="?xx=prepositions/prepositions">preposition</a>.</p>-->
            <p>Some examples as complement of the progressive particle <a href="?gd=ag"
                    ><g>ag</g></a> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha Màiri <m>ag obair</m> agus tha Calum <m>ag obair</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary is working and Malcolm is working.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha Màiri agus Calum <m>ag obair</m> anns an achadh an diugh.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary and Malcolm are working in the field today.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 6–7</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha Màiri sgìth. Tha i <m>sgìth ag obair</m> anns an achadh.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary is tired.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha sibh <m>trang ag obair</m> anns an achadh agus tha sibh sgìth.</gd>
                        <tr>You are busy working in the field and you are tired.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
